headline: Regional Banks’ Preferred Prices Swing on Credit Losses
summary: The preferred shares of Zions on Thursday slumped by the most since May 2023 to their lowest level in 18 months, while an issue by Western Alliance dropped the most since April 2024. Equities on Friday edged mildly higher, helped by solid results from Truist Financial Corp., Regions Financial Corp. and Fifth Third Bancorp.

headline: Bank Stocks Recoup Some Losses as Earnings Ease Credit Fears
summary: The modest rebound follows a 6.3% plunge on Thursday, led by Zions and Western Alliance Bancorp after they said they were victims of fraud on loans to funds that invest in distressed commercial mortgages.  The latest crop of earnings helped abate concerns of credit stress spreading across the group following the high-profile bankruptcies of auto lender Tricolor Holdings and car-parts supplier First Brands Group.  Truist Financial Corp., Regions Financial Corp. and Fifth Third Bancorp all jumped after reporting lower provisions for credit losses than analysts expected.

headline: Wall Street steadies after its slide as banks recover some of their losses
summary: The U.S. stock market seems to be steadying on Friday, as banks recover some of their sharp losses from the day before.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average was up 198 points, or 0.4%, as of 12:49 p.m. Eastern time, and the Nasdaq composite was 0.3% higher.  All three indexes drifted between gains and losses through the morning, but the moves weren't as jarring as the big hour-to-hour swings they had earlier in the week.
